<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
  >
<body>

<metal:portlets fill-slot="portlets">
  <tal:portlet
    replace="structure view/distribution/@@+portlet-ppa-architectures" />
</metal:portlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <h1>Personal Package Archive Activation</h1>

  <p>
    A PPA is a place where you can build and publish your own packages.
    These can be custom versions of Ubuntu packages, or completely new
    packages, and can be built for any <a href="/ubuntu/">supported
    version of Ubuntu</a>. For more information, please see the
    <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/PPAQuickStart">PPA Quick Start
    Guide</a>.
  </p>

  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">

    <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info">
       <p>
         Read the current version of
         <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/PPATermsofUse">PPA Terms of
         Use</a> before activating your PPA.
       </p>
    </div>

    <div class="form" metal:fill-slot="widgets">

      <div tal:define="widget nocall:view/widgets/accepted|nothing"
           tal:condition="widget" style="padding-bottom: 1em">
        <metal:widget metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/widget_row" />
      </div>

      <div tal:define="widget nocall:view/widgets/description|nothing"
           tal:condition="widget">
         <metal:widget metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/widget_row" />
      </div>

   </div>

  <div class="actions" metal:fill-slot="buttons">
    <input tal:replace="structure view/actions/field.actions.cancel/render" />
    <input tal:replace="structure view/actions/field.actions.activate/render" />
  </div>

  </div>

</div>

    <p metal:fill-slot="help">
       Once you activate your PPA you will be able to upload source
       packages to it and Launchpad will build and publish their
       binaries for you. Check the procedure details in the
       quick-start <a href="https://help.launchpad.net/PPAQuickStart"
       >guide</a>.
    </p>

</body>
</html>
